    "reviews_attribution": "Reseñas verificadas por AtoC Korea. 4.8/5 average across 142 verified bookings.",
    "unesco_fit_note": "unesco_fit=3: Hallasan is a ユネスコ Biosphere Reserve and the centerpiece of the Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes World Heritage inscription, but the tour visits the 1100 Highland scenic zone (drive-up viewing area), not the inscribed lava tube system or the summit hike.",
    "competing_products": [
      "jeju-grand-highlights-loop",
      "jeju-southern-top-unesco-spots-tour",
      "jeju-west-south-full-day-authentic-tour",
      "jeju-hydrangea-festival-tour-southwest-route"
    ],
    "audit_summary": "Southwest Jeju loop covering ユネスコ Hallasan (Eoseungsaengak), south-coast volcanic geology (Daepo Jusangjeolli), Joseon Daoist mythology (Cheonjeyeon Seven Nymphs), Korea's largest tea field (Osulloc / AmorePacific), and the west-coast sunset cafe strip (Aewol). Lifestyle-anchored counterpart to the highlights-loop sister tour: shares Hallasan + Jusangjeolli openers, diverges into tea + cafe + sunset territory.",
    "score_rationale": {
      "high_scores": {
        "first_time_jeju_fit=0.95": "Strong intro covering ユネスコ + geology + culture in one day, slightly behind highlights-loop only on Triple-ユネスコ Seongsan absence",
        "honeymoon_fit=1.0": "Sunset finale at Aewol + cafe culture + tea heritage = strongest honeymoon framing in the catalog",
        "tea_culture_fit=1.0": "Seogwang plantation = Korea's largest green-tea field; Amorepacific brand depth",
        "sunset_photography_fit=1.0": "West-facing Aewol horizon + cafe rooftop terraces — single best sunset stop in the southwest catalog",
        "cafe_culture_fit=1.0": "30+ cafes on a 5 km strip — Korea's densest sea-view cafe row",
        "lifestyle_traveler_fit=1.0": "Modern Jeju identity (Amorepacific, K-drama filming, sunset cafes) anchors the back half of the day"
      },
      "low_scores": {
        "private_tour_fit=0.05": "Format is small-group fixed itinerary only",
        "triple_unesco_fit=0.05": "Seongsan deliberately absent — that's the highlights-loop sister tour",
        "east_jeju_fit=0.05": "Loop deliberately excludes east coast",
        "thrill_seekers_fit=0.05": "Pace is contemplative; no adventure activities"
      }
    },
    "differentiation_vs_highlights_loop_sister": "Same Hallasan + Jusangjeolli openers, but **southwest-coastal anchor terminating at Aewol** (sister terminates at east-coast Seongsan Triple ユネスコ). This tour = tea + cafe + sunset lifestyle emphasis; sister = ユネスコ + geology emphasis. **Honeymoon + lifestyle traveler fit = highest in catalog** for southwest framing, with sunset photography window calibrated to 17:30–18:30 spring/autumn arrivals at Aewol. Pair complementarily on 2-day Jeju itineraries: this tour Day 1 (lifestyle anchor), sister Day 2 (ユネスコ anchor) — or vice versa depending on which ユネスコ-vs-cafe priority guests want first.",
